A220_INDICES_FILE

private java.lang.String A220_INDICES_FILE
This represents the file that contains the indices associated with the A220 protocol. It should reside in the same directory as the calling application. The format for this file must be correct in order for it to be processed correctly.

C220_INDICES_FILE

private java.lang.String C220_INDICES_FILE
This represents the file that contains the indices associated with the C220 protocol. It should reside in the same directory as the calling application. The format for this file must be correct in order for it to be processed correctly.

A220TYPESFILE

private java.lang.String A220TYPESFILE
This represents the file that contains the types associated with the A220 protocol. It should reside in the same directory as the calling application. The format for this file must be correct in order for it to be processed correctly.

C220TYPESFILE

private java.lang.String C220TYPESFILE
This represents the file that contains the types associated with the C220 protocol. It should reside in the same directory as the calling application. The format for this file must be correct in order for it to be processed correctly.

SELECTED_INDICES_FILE

private java.lang.String SELECTED_INDICES_FILE
This represents the file that contains the indices selected by the operator. It will reside in the /h/AFATDS/data/scratch directory. This file is generated by this class and then processed by an Ada program; so, it is important to maintain its format. Any changes to the format must be coordinated between this class and the Ada driver that reads this file.

RESULTS_FILE

private java.lang.String RESULTS_FILE
This represents the file that contains the results generated by the Ada program and which are read in by this class and displayed in the resultsPanel. It will reside in the /h/AFATDS/data/scratch directory. This file is generated by the Ada driver; so, it is important to maintain its format. Any changes to the format must be coordinated between Ada driver that creates this file and this class. IMPORTANT: The path to this file reference must be the same fullpath provided by the Ada driver!

protocolNames

private final java.lang.String[] protocolNames
This array contains the names of the protocols to be tested. Each item in the array should have its own set of indices and types files.
